  "local_port": 59386,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the requirements to attend the Berkshire Hathaway Annual Shareholder Meeting?",
  "response": "Attending the Berkshire Hathaway Annual Shareholders Meeting, often dubbed the \"Woodstock for Capitalists,\" is a coveted opportunity for investors and enthusiasts alike. Here's a comprehensive guide to the requirements and steps to attend:\n\n### 1. **Be a Berkshire Hathaway Shareholder**\n\n- **Ownership Requirement**: To attend the meeting, you must own Berkshire Hathaway (BRK.A or BRK.B) shares. The number of shares required is typically modest, and there is no minimum threshold beyond being a shareholder of record.\n  \n- **Record Date**: Ensure you purchase and hold the shares before the **record date** set by Berkshire Hathaway. This date determines which shareholders are eligible to attend the meeting.\n\n### 2. **Register in Advance**\n\n- **Online Registration**: Registration usually opens several weeks before the event. Visit the [Berkshire Hathaway Annual Meeting](https://www.berkshirehathaway.com/) official website to access the registration portal.\n  \n- **Login Credentials**: You will need to provide your shareholder information, which may include your name, shareholder number, and possibly details from your brokerage account.\n  \n- **Registration Deadline**: Pay attention to registration deadlines. Seats are limited and tend to fill up quickly, so registering early increases your chances.\n\n### 3. **Meeting Details**\n\n- **Location**: The meeting is traditionally held at the **CHI Health Center Omaha** in Omaha, Nebraska. Ensure you have travel arrangements in place well in advance.\n\n- **Date and Time**: The meeting is typically held in early May. Check the official website or your shareholder communications for the exact date and schedule.\n\n### 4. **Accommodations and Travel**\n\n- **Travel Arrangements**: Book your flights and accommodations early, as hotels in Omaha are often fully booked due to the influx of attendees.\n  \n- **Local Transportation**: Plan how you will get from your accommodation to the meeting venue. Options may include rental cars, ride-sharing services, or public transportation.\n\n### 5. **Prepare for the Meeting**\n\n- **Dress Code**: Business casual is generally appropriate, though some attendees choose to dress more formally.\n  \n- **Materials**: Bring your shareholder statement, a form of identification, and any necessary documents required during registration.\n  \n- **Questions**: If you wish to ask questions during the Q&A session, prepare them in advance. Note that questions are typically submitted in writing before the meeting.\n\n### 6. **Attend Virtually (If Applicable)**\n\n- **Virtual Access**: In some cases, especially considering fluctuations like public health concerns, Berkshire Hathaway may offer virtual attendance options. Check the latest information on the official website.\n  \n- **Participation**: Virtual attendees might have the opportunity to submit questions online and watch live streams of the proceedings.\n\n### 7. **Costs to Consider**\n\n- **Ticket Fees**: While the event is primarily for shareholders, there might be nominal fees for access or specific seating sections. Verify any associated costs during registration.\n  \n- **Travel Expenses**: Budget for transportation, lodging, meals, and any other personal expenses during your trip to Omaha.\n\n### 8. **Health and Safety Guidelines**\n\n- **Current Protocols**: Stay informed about any health and safety guidelines or requirements, such as vaccination status or mask mandates, which may be in place at the time of the meeting.\n  \n- **Preparedness**: Bring any necessary health documents or supplies as required by the event organizers.\n\n### 9. **Stay Updated**\n\n- **Official Communications**: Regularly check Berkshire Hathaway\u2019s official channels\u2014such as their website, shareholder newsletters, and official press releases\u2014for the most current information regarding the annual meeting.\n  \n- **Contact Information**: If you have questions or need assistance, reach out to Berkshire Hathaway's shareholder services through their official contact points.\n\n### Summary\n\nTo attend the Berkshire Hathaway Annual Shareholders Meeting, you must be a registered shareholder as of the specified record date, complete the registration process in advance, arrange for travel and accommodations to Omaha, and comply with any event-specific requirements or guidelines. Given the event's popularity and limited seating, proactive planning and early registration are essential to secure your spot.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, always refer to the [official Berkshire Hathaway Annual Meeting page](https://www.berkshirehathaway.com/).",
  "response_tokens": [
